To Leonard Brugier &quot;Hunkapi&quot; a relative (without need of ceremony):<br>
I served in Viet Nam in 1966-67-69 as an assault helicopter pilot. I am Comanche-Lakota and I live in Chelsea, OK.  I know many honorable Native American Viet Nam veterans who live in this area from many different tribes.<br>
I do a lot of work in the disciplines of psychology and education, particularily in the subject of Post Traumatic Stress Disorders.<br>
There is much to be gained from our forefathers in dealing with the aftermath of warfare and that wisdom should be shared.<br>
If I can help you in gathering our brothers for a &quot;Wiping of The Tears&quot; ceremony, please contact me at Edward Ramon, Route 1 Box 335-1, Chelsea, OK 74016.<br>
Pila maye, mita Kola, akicita was`te. Akita mani yo. Welcome home!
